docs/impl/wp_sched_review/logs/S5_T2.2_review.1.stdout.log:8:`waveplan-cli` resolves `--review-schedule` then discards it (`_ = _resolve_review_schedule_path(...)`) for `next`, `step`, `run`, `journal`. Subprocess `tool_args` never include `--review-schedule`. The Go binaries `cmd/swim-next/main.go`, `cmd/swim-step/main.go`, `cmd/swim-run/main.go`, `cmd/swim-journal/main.go` define no `--review-schedule` flag and never read `WAVEPLAN_SCHED_REVIEW`. Result: `ResolveNext` always sees `ReviewSchedulePath=""`, sidecar never merged, block never fires outside Go tests.
docs/impl/wp_sched_review/logs/S5_T2.2_review.1.stdout.log:41:3. **HIGH-1 / HIGH-2**: explicitly defer to T3.2 with a one-line note in the plan + journal, OR add `--review-schedule` flag + `WAVEPLAN_SCHED_REVIEW` env read to the four Go binaries and the four Python subprocess `tool_args` lists, plus an installed-CLI test that proves the block reaches `swim run` end-to-end. Reviewer recommendation: at minimum, document deferral in the implementer's handoff to T3.2 so T2.2's block is not silently dead.
